adjectives.description: presential (comparative more presential, superlative most presential)

entries.meaning: in-person, on-premises, face-to-face (i.e., not involving online, virtual or remote interaction)
(now rare) Implying actual presence; present. [from 15th c.]
examples: Going a foote, I shall durty my selfe up to my waste; and little men, going alongst our streets, are subject (for want of presentiall apparence) to be justled or elbowed.

entries.meaning: (grammar, now rare) Pertaining to the present tense. [from 19th c.]
